author: Lester Teo
text: AF Upper Cross St recently completed renovations and need to do justice to the previous poor reviews. Updated gym flooring, machines, free weights, no suspicious smells, spacious training area on L2, but most impressed at the spanking new showers with wet/dry areas and vanity section. Well done by the management! But my favourite outlet is still AF Orchard cause of the Dyson hairdryer.

author: Daniel47829
text: Hakem is a great Manager at this Anytime location. He cares about his clients and he is very patient and polite. The gym is small but offers all what it needs for strength and endurance sessions.

author: Alexander Yip
text: Would be a 0 star if not because of the minimum, but hey! If you guys considering of sign up for gym, dont sign up anytime fitness because the staff will not be responsible to help you, they will push to each other and eventually become the member's fault. So its basically like I paid money to get poor service. What a great experience!

author: Theodore Levitt
text:
Well equipped gym. Convenient location. Staff are mostly friendly. Crowd is fair and decent.

Equipments are not well maintained. Ceilings are leaking. Overall maintenance is poor. Toilets smell bad and facilities are breaking down.

Can be improved with some minor touch up. Hope the gym owner can look into it.

author: Degen Hill
text: Gym has everything you need. Odd pricing structure. 148 for a month, plus 135 for signup fee, plus 70 for key card. I paid 70 per week, with 50 for key deposit. Has 2 stories, and wasn‚Äôt too busy at 9am. Cardio, free weights, cable machines, and nice squat rack.

author: Vin
text:
The gym is a short 5-minute walk away from Chinatown MRT.

The gym spans two floors. The first floor houses most of the equipment, and the second is largely a CrossFit area with 7 individual shower rooms (3 male, 2 female and 2 unisex). From the well-worn interior, it's apparent that the outlet is old.

Unlike most other Anytime Fitness outlets, the music selection here is tasteful and should satisfy the average gym patron. There are also lockers that are free to use.

My only gripe about this outlet is that the shower room doesn't have a stool of sorts so that patrons can put their belongings while showering. We'd have to hang out bags from hooks behind the door.

author: Zavier Teo
text:
Terrible management, will force a predatory 15% upcharge of monthly fees if there are any issues with their payment provider. Seems like they enjoy gouging their loyal customers for their own financial benefit.

Equipments here are barely maintained, most seats show signs of wear and falling apart equipment is the norm here.

Have seen plenty of cockroaches roaming around the gym.

Recently "upgraded" but no upkeep is done, toilets are filthy, smelly and disgusting. Sink area is constantly covered in hair. Toilet seats covered in urine. No ventilation in the cubicles as well.

author: write
text:
I have called several times to change payment details and yet to receive any responses, now I am charged with $15 for late payment fee when the staff dont bother to help me before the deduction date.

Yet this gym have the face to report me to Singapore Commercial Credit Bureau, they banned my account and still expect me to pay them for 4 months of membership when Im not even using it.

Guys, pls dont listen to whatever the staff said from anytime fitness, they are SCAMMER!

author: ŸÅŸäÿµŸÑ ÿßŸÑÿ≥ŸÑŸÖŸä
text:
What a rude guy, Hakim is disrespectful person
I went to know the daypass but he act aggressively.

Not recommended for people come to do meetings in SG

author: Genta
text: Anytime Fitness Upper Cross Street beckons fitness enthusiasts with its state-of-the-art facilities and round-the-clock access, catering to busy schedules and health-conscious travelers alike. Stepping into the gym, I found myself immersed in a world of fitness and wellness, surrounded by top-of-the-line equipment and dedicated trainers ready to assist with personalized workouts. Whether I was squeezing in a late-night session or starting my day with an energizing workout, Anytime Fitness Upper Cross Street provided the perfect environment for achieving my fitness goals.

author: Thai Nguyen
text: Headcoach Anthony assisted us, he was very friendly üôèüèª. The machines here are all Hammer Strength and Lifefitness, the gym is clean, comfortable and a great place to work out. ‚Ä¶

author: Carolina Perez
text: In a total pity that a chain with so much prestige as Anytime fitness has this branch so terribly disgusting I had already had bad reviews about this branch but do not take it seriously today I decided since it is close to work but it was a terrible disappointment it is the first and last time that I stop in that branch it is very extremely dirty neglected when I go up to shower the shower area is disgusting cockroaches, hair everywhere smells like horrible humidity I asked the person who cleans to help me clean the shower since I would bathe there later and with a terrible attitude he refused and told me that my things would get wet and dirty in the same way what kind of staff and attitude is that I would not return to that place even if they paid me

author: J L
text:
Just an okay gym convenient for post-work hours gym sessions. 2nd floor is poorly utilised with racks but no proper padding and enough plates which could have been used for more types of lifting other than squats. So most people are just on the 2nd floor for random core workouts.
Biggest flaw of the gym is the lack of enforcement by staff to tell people to put back their weights. Lots of ignorant and inconsiderate gym goers here but well what can you do; it‚Äôs either this or Cecil st gym. Would go somewhere if I could

author: Alex D
text:
I won‚Äôt dwell on the negative reviews about the moldy toilets since that‚Äôs been covered enough already.

As a long-time member visiting this branch for the first time, I actually had to stop my workout halfway through and head to another branch just to finish it. The way this gym is set up is really strange compared to others.

Like many have said, the second floor is empty, and all the foot traffic is on the first floor. Yet the only water dispenser is on the second floor.

There are three power racks but only one bench available.

In the dumbbell area, there‚Äôs only one adjustable bench, while the rest are flat benches, which would‚Äôve made more sense in the power rack area.

Lastly, the cable pulley section doesn‚Äôt even have a rope handle. There are four pulley machines, but the most commonly used attachments are missing. The other AF branches have plenty of them.

It‚Äôs as if the gym manager doesn‚Äôt even work out and has no clue how things should function.

author: muse rosli
text: AF member from Malaysia. The location is quite strategic and walking distance from nearby hotel. Obviously the range of equipment almost the same as other clubs. Clean and well sorted equipment. Looking forward to visit again.

author: spencer soh
text: Used to be their outlet member before transferring to other outlet in 2019. Getting invoice / receipt via email request alway took couple of days. Visited them last week after 2 years and was shocked, ceiling paints cracking dropping all over. Machines badly maintained, limited sanitisers and cleaning towels, lastly toilet dirty and not maintained too.

author: itschesterrific
text:
foreigner here.
im glad their equipments are complete :)
clean and spacious
AC is just cold (maybe it's because there aint n't many people around when im there)

author: M C
text: Such a terrible gym with no cleaning staff and full of dust in changing room!

author: Sienna V
text:
oh my God the state of the toilets. Black mould everywhere! Poor drainage literally 0 venilation, for some reason there are 2 doors within a tiny shower.

Can management remove some panelling and allow the water to evaporate? The current state of the showers is like a steam room, and I bet it's a bacteria breeding ground. Health hazard.

Despite it being newly renovated, the toilets were just an afterthought. This AF is run by RFT group, so they have hairdryers from 1980s just like their yishun & nex branch.

4 sets of very old hairdryers instead of 1 higher model hairdryers. Also, one of the old dryers is broken.

Machine and weight room are good though.

author: Duy Nguyen
text: Very nice gym with good equipment, kind staff always willing to help people

author: Su Lee
text: Love this place. There are 2 levels and the upper level is quiet. Can do stretching and free weights üòç There are shower rooms too ‚Ä¶

author: Amos Lam
text: Worst ever Branch. Should just closed it down. No locker and have to pay for it. Disgusting branch. Saw this branch added to my stronger intention to exit membership.

author: Bill Adamec
text: Just visited on their ‚Äúone time use‚Äù pass. Very nice facility with everything I needed, and the staff is incredibly accommodating and friendly. Will definitely go back to this location during my next visit!

author: Alfred Chan
text: One of my favourite branches after they got rid of a particular PT. Nicely renovated but the number of toilets (1 per gender) doesn't help with the convenience and is possibly why bathrooms have urine smell. Equipment wise is great and the overall gym ambience is healthy and supportive.

author: James Chan
text: Visited the gym today. It is newly renovated with nice layout. However, there was one guy who hold on to 2 benches and a pulley for his workout. When I approached him to share the benches, he just ignored and continued on. Later on, this heavily tattooed guy still came to argue and said his workout needed all those benches. It's absolutely shocking to meet such an individual. I also noticed all the other users stayed a distance away from this guy when he was do his workout. It may be good for the gym to monitor their users basic etiquette.

author: balan vinayagan
text:
So far toilets need to be improved,  Will require some add one of cloths hanging Knobs, and stool  to be placed at each toilet. Hair dryer facility and the host pipes near toilet bowl are weak.

Other then that , the gym have most of the equipments which makes me more satisfied.

Dear gym owner, please take a look on the toilets portion on the mentioned areas.

author: Tropical_storm X
text:
Small but new. Opens 24 hours. Most of the guests are male but very limited numbers of male toilets while the female toilets are always empty. Ridiculous situation leading to men queuing for toilets while the female designated toilets are always empty. Note that the toilets are individual private rooms, not shared. Why the need to segregate? Serves no purpose except to appease some arbitrary sensitivities

#update
Gym is starting to feel run down. Paint peeling on the ceiling and the air quality is suspect. Sadness. Gym is seriously in need of maintenance

author: Jiayi Ong
text:
This will be my first and last time visiting the outlet. The outlet has a mouldy smell and it smell like a rundown KTV with cigarette smell. Those who have sinus or sensitive nose issues, you may avoid because the carpet flooring is poorly maintained. The cleanliness was not well maintained as equipment was not properly clean and you still can see sweat marks on the equipments. People hogging the equipment and sometimes multiple equipment at one time. This make the experience terrible.

The toilet has a strong sewage pungent and condition is comparable to a public toilet. Not sure anyone working at this outlet but it just felt like an outlet left abandoned.

author: Ms.J Hassim
text: have been coming to this outlet pre reno and post reno. they did some great things with the toilet and shower yeah no big deal. but one I don‚Äôt get is they have this massive (what I‚Äôd call it) functional training space at L2.. yes I get it, it‚Äôs gym rules to have proper footwear when training, especially when dealing with weights. here‚Äôs the thing: some people train barefoot as part of their conditioning. it‚Äôs backed by evidence that barefoot training have it‚Äôs positive side. previous management are all about supporting their members in their journey. the new people from of current management though, not only they are the only AF staffs that don‚Äôt smile to their members, they‚Äôre almost like snobs. today i got told off I need to wear shoes when training at L2. Sure, I was only doing some ATG squats, dead hangs, cossacks and i probably weigh 135lbs so perhaps I am a threat to myself /s. I wore my shoes thereafter. No big deal i thought, except it was. For the last 10 times I been there, I‚Äôve been bare footing whilst training not until 19/1/24, right. Soon, came a dude who was in Slippers and the footwear police didn‚Äôt come and tell him off to wear his shoes so I reckon it‚Äôs more like; If you‚Äôre gonna do barefoot, don‚Äôt let the staff see you?. In hindsight perhaps they felt it‚Äôs their duty to enforce club rules, don‚Äôt know. It differs between different staffs too I guess. Since not everyone‚Äôs a footwear police. the Guy PT didn‚Äôt bat an eye the few times he saw me barefooted? I‚Äôve been to a few other AF branches, old and new and all ran by different groups. all of them smiled and greeted any members that walked in their gym.. Especially the guys not too far from their neighbourhood, AF Bugis. I loved coming to UCS branch cause they had solid racks for people who train functional and bodyweight like me (they have a gymnastics ring which they didn‚Äôt dispose off from the previous guys) and that was a plus, big time. they didn‚Äôt bother me much with barefooting, even when they did that one time, they were polite. and EXCUSE ME, we‚Äôre the paying members of your gym, if you were to reinforce footwear at least do it politely. Now I‚Äôm not even planning to come back and hope I tapped in enough at other branch so my membership gets converted to others, anywhere BUT UCS. Good luck maintaining your old members. slowly starting to see less familiar faces in that branch. whilst a gym as small as Queensway shopping still have the familiar faces from pre pandemic.

author: Jan Rothkegel
text: Just joined the gym yesterday. Not really used to having the key fob (which is charged with $85 and non-refundable even after membership ends) with me yet, so forgot it at home, which is my bad. As I was already at the studio, I went in and thought it‚Äôd be okay as I‚Äôm a member. Could show ID + my contact. But don‚Äôt expect any support from them - trainer Kimberly rushed towards me and kicked me straight out in a very rude manner. Explained the situation but didn‚Äôt even listen to me. Note to myself - paying the extra dollars for Pure or Virgin, where I am treated as a member, is worth it.

author: Stephanie Goh
text: gym staff like to off the ac and only switch on one of them! This isnt the first reminder to switch the AC on  and there weren't such issues w the old staffing. miss the old staffing! they are more considerate as compared to the new one.

author: Zavier
text:
Gym is well equipped. However, giving 2 stars because the gym really needs some serious maintenance, especially the toilets.

It's not the cleaner's fault tho, as I always see the cleaner cleaning the toilets.

author: Clems G
text:
Last visited this AF outlet back in ~2020?
Old layout was dark and had poor equipment placements (hard to reach around etc.)

Just visited again in Aug 2023, their outlet has underwent much renov and the toilets are gery spacious and well lit. :)

Sadly, this AF outlet doesn't have the best air circulation, their a/c isn't cold enough + fans not switched on (perhaps most members here are used to the temperature here?)

author: Zezian Chin
text: Perhaps management could consider to improve the air quality of the gym. The outlet has a mouldy smell. The carpet flooring is poorly maintained may be the reason causing the weird smell in the gym.

author: YETI_97
text: This gym is a good gym however I noticed something recently that has been bothering me. I stay at CCK but I do frequent this gym as it is in the vicinity of where I work during after office hours at around 7. There is this middle aged Chinese gentleman with a beard(not that I have any issues with his age) wearing singlet and spandex that trains around this timing as well for 3-4 hours. He would pace around the gym with his headphones on and grunt excessively loud as well as obnoxiously slam the weights especially on the lat pulldown machine causing a distraction to other gym members and even frightening some to the point where they feel uncomfortable to train near him and would physically move to the other side of the gym. I understand if he grunts when the weight is heavy but he does it even when the weight is relatively light. He would also pace around the gym and stare at other members giving off a very intimidating vibe. I am astounded that the staff ignores his lack of gym etiquette and I can say this would be a reason for me to not return to the gym. I really hope the staff would give him a verbal warning because I myself have seen other members especially females feel really intimidated by him and I am sure they have lodged a complaint as well. Hope to see some follow up on this because I really like this outlet!

author: Fuyi Devt
text:
Since their feedback station conveniently lacks a pen or pencil, i resort to a Google review: -
1. All toilet bins have broken lids
2. All hand-held showers are leaking
3. All toilet roll holders are broken
4. Only 1 toilet has a bench to sit/ place bag
5. All WC covers are scratched and dirtied
6. Hand sanitizer has been empty for 2 weeks.

Having said that, I have no issue with the rest of the gym. Gym equipment, as far I know, are of good quality.

author: Riduwan Abu Bakar
text: Gym or Gay Sauna? When I went to the gym at 11am on 26th Aug 2025, 2 guys came out from the WC at the same time. Both wash their hands and gargle their mouths afterward. Gym toilet turns sleezy.

author: Savannah F
text:
Really dirty. Was charged $25 as a visitors for a gross gym and rude service.  To be charged so much and not have a half decent space to work out is a joke. I‚Äôm moving to Singapore and do not recommend you go here as a local or a tourist. Clean your equipment! Disgusting.

Because I can reply to the passive aggressive comment that was just left by a staff member I will leave it here.

If the gym is so clean than why are there 2-3 other RECENT Reviews stating otherwise? One written 5 days before mine? And yes I was at the time a tourist visitor. But this location does not live up to Anytime fitness standards  (which I have been to in MULTIPLE countries) it is  for this reason why I was upset about having to pay the $25. But to be fair I should have walked around the gym before paying. It‚Äôs my fault for having faith that the gym would live up to decent hygiene expectations ESPECIALLY IN SINGAPORE. This should be a well maintained gym considering where it‚Äôs located and how ‚Äúnew‚Äù it is. It‚Äôs even more appalling because the gym is new you would expect it to be good quality. Not to mention there is little to no staff member present and the one that was there was abrasive and rude ( also noted in OTHER people‚Äôs comments) you guys clearly need to up your standards people have commented saying the bathrooms made them want to puke so my apologies for not going into further details about the disgusting state of the gym. I hope for Corprates sake you guys improve the gym and keep it well maintained and CLEAN otherwise I‚Äôm sure these types of post will continue (hence the last few). Thanks for responding though at least you are doing one thing right!

author: Daniel
text: I‚Äôm interested to join for a membership but it seems the office is always locked. Looked around there‚Äôs no way to get in. Even the members inside can‚Äôt really help. Tried to call the number but none picked up. Not sure how this business operates.

author: Lovemusic111
text:
met this sales/pt who cheated me to sign the contract, what he explained and promised is totally different from what was written on the contract, and then left the gym.

Though this created troubles for me, and went through quite a long way to get response from the gym, but this yr the management and staff seemed to have changed and solved the problem pretty quickly.

For people who want to sign up here, just need to take note and be careful of certain pt and read the contract carefully before signing. The gym itself was fine and well equipped.

author: Robin Ong
text:
Lots of equipment within a small space. Was not too crowded when I visited on a weekday at 1pm.

Would have appreciated having a water dispenser on the ground floor instead of having to go up to level 2 each time I needed to fill my bottle.

author: Lynn Lynn Oo
text:
Syarif is an excellent coach, always bringing to the
table plenty of knowledge, experience and
enthusiasm. He has helped me in
achieving my goals in strength and mobility.
Throughout the time I have trained with him he has
always been very professional, a fun personality to
train with and always makes the workouts
interesting and challenging.

And the club is clean, neat, lots of equipment and open 24 hrs ü§©

author: Lin Kaixiang
text: The gym is conveniently located and equipments are great. However, I encountered a very rude and unprofessional personal trainer not sure if she knows what is proper body language/professionalism. While I was half way through a set she told me to put on my shoes, understood where she was coming from I asked politely if I could put it on after my current set. She replied rudely "no u have to put it on now!". I obliged without any hesitation. However, when I was leaving the gym we bumped into one another and I tried to be friendly and said "bye" she simply rolled her eyes and walked away. I am not sure having such personal trainer to represent this brand and branch is an ideal move. A gesture like that totally ruined my impression and experience here. She has forgotten that customers see her as a brand representative , yet she chose to live in her single frame thinking and assuming that she actually owns the place. Please don't not forget we are your pay master. It will not hurt to be polite and friendly.

author: Andrea Vu
text: super super super dirty gym, as in the dirtiest gym I have ever been. I'm a 12 months contract member and already want to give up. On my first trial day, things were dirty but still acceptable, then become worst and worst. I'm a frequently work out type and I come to the gym everyday early morning and I have not seen anything more cleaner here at this outlet :(

author: Darragh Lenihan
text:
Gym just been completely renovated and reopened 8th June 23.

Old equipment has been replaced. Everything brand new.

Awesome gym, really nice people, amazing location.

author: Jun Wei Soong
text:
The roof leaking problem is serious, because many leaks are directly above the fitness equipment, so many equipment cannot be used.
The toilet smells bad and the garbage in the trash can is gone for a long time and still no one has cleaned it up

author: Mike M
text: Good selection of free weights and machines. Fairly large space on two separate level. Poorly maintained changing and shower facilities wth poor ventilation. Only seven stalls available (5 unisex and 2 female only). Occasionally long queues and waiting times (average 0-5 mins but can be 10+ mins from time to time).

author: Will Scardova
text: Don‚Äôt come to this place. They provide a free trial in the website and after register they refuse you access and you have to pay anyway.

author: Johnny Azzurro
text: Here is temporarily closed for renovation. They never mentioned until when the renovation is finished.

author: Ezzat Danial
text: gym is at an easily accessible location, large enough to support a decent number of people. well functioning equipment and helpful staff too.

author: Nithi Tangsirisap
text: Renovated already, and now it's very clean and organised. Got all the fundamental equipment you would need for proper weight training.

author: Bethany Ann
text: Such a great gym, has everything you need and more. Changing rooms are amazing

author: Maria Quek
text: Got so used to being able to work out till 11pm. New closing  time is at 10pm. Management could have put up a notice to inform patrons of new closing time. If i had known, i would have not bothered coming in.

text: 33 SGD for a One-Day Guestpass is expensive price. The Studio isnt that greate.
